==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aldebaran
<hw>Al*deb"a*ran</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l*d⟦ecr⟧b"⟦adot⟧*r⟦acr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. <ets>al-debar⟦amac⟧n</ets>, fr.
<ets>dabar</ets> to follow; so called because this star follows upon the
Pleiades.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A red star of the first
magnitude, situated in the eye of Taurus; the Bull's Eye. It is the
bright star in the group called the <membof>Hyades</membof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now when <qex>Aldebaran</qex> was mounted high⟦br⟧
Above the shiny Cassiopeia's chair.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aldehyde</ent>⟦br⟧
